ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.298                Enzyme
NAME        anthocyanidin 3-O-glucoside 5-O-glucosyltransferase;
            UDP-glucose:anthocyanin 5-O-glucosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-glucose:anthocyanidin-3-O-beta-D-glucoside 5-O-glucosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-glucose + an anthocyanidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside = UDP + an anthocyanidin 3,5-di-O-beta-D-glucoside [RN:R10262]
ALL_REAC    R10262 > R06546 R07874 R07911;
            (other) R06547
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-glucose [CPD:C00029];
            anthocyanidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C15539]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            anthocyanidin 3,5-di-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C06361]
COMMENT     Isolated from the plants Perilla frutescens var. crispa, Verbena hybrida [1], Dahlia variabilis [2] and Gentiana triflora (clustered gentian) [3]. It will also act on anthocyanidin 3-O-(6-O-malonylglucoside) [2] and is much less active with hydroxycinnamoylglucose derivatives [3]. There is no activity in the absence of the 3-O-glucoside group.
